# Accessibility & 508 compliance rules

Apply these to every component and page without being asked.

## Semantic HTML
- One `<h1>` per page — the page title only
- Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` appropriately
- Never use a `<div>` or `<span>` for something that should be a `<button>`, `<a>`, or form element
- All interactive elements must be reachable and operable via keyboard

## Images and icons
- Every `<img>` needs a descriptive `alt` attribute
- Decorative images use `alt=""`
- Inline SVG icons used as buttons need `aria-label` on the parent button
- SVG icons that are purely decorative need `aria-hidden="true"`

## Forms and inputs
- Every `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>` needs an associated `<label>`
- Use `htmlFor` / `id` pairing — never rely on placeholder text as a label
- Error messages must be associated with their input via `aria-describedby`

## Color and contrast
- Text on white background: minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio (WCAG AA)
- Large text (18px+ or 14px+ bold): minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- Never use color alone to convey meaning — always pair with text or icon
- Brand colors in use:
  - Slate #1c2333 on white: passes AAA
  - Amber #BA7517 on white: passes AA for large text only — do NOT use for body text
  - Amber text on white: use #8B5E10 (darker) for small text if needed

## Focus management
- Never remove focus outlines (`outline: none`) without providing a visible alternative
- Use Tailwind's `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2` pattern
- Modal/dialog focus must be trapped inside while open

## ARIA
- Don't add ARIA roles to semantic elements that already have them (`<button>` doesn't need `role="button"`)
- Use `aria-current="page"` on the active nav link
- Use `aria-expanded` on disclosure/accordion triggers
- Use `aria-live` regions for dynamic content updates (filter results, notifications)

## Navigation
- Skip-to-main-content link as the very first focusable element on every page
- Nav links must indicate current page via `aria-current="page"`
- Mobile nav toggle must have descriptive `aria-label` ("Open menu" / "Close menu")
- Mobile nav must be keyboard navigable and closeable with Escape key

## Links
- Never use "click here" or "read more" as link text — link text must describe the destination
- External links should indicate they open in a new tab if `target="_blank"` is used
- `target="_blank"` always paired with `rel="noopener noreferrer"`